$interpreted: : Kingdom of the Sun Calendar, year 177
Sherlock: ...When the heck is this war going to end?
Sherlock: The Bazaar wasn't exactly bustling to begin with. If this war keeps going on, we are all screwed!
Sherlock: But~ thanks to the war, I was able to get my hands on some armor and weapons. These sell for a good price, lucky me~
Sherlock: An orphan on the battlefield? Shoo, shoo, leave me alone. Stop bothering me.
Sherlock: I said leave me alone! I don't care if you're a child; I'll punch you in the face!
Soldier: A mechanican!? The Desert Kingdom and the Mechanical Territory are working together now?
Sherlock: What? I am not affiliated with the Mechanical Territory. The war is between you guys and the Desert Kingdom.
Sherlock: Don't get me involved with your horse crap!
Soldier: Then what the heck are you doing!
Sherlock: Recovering his armor and weapons, because I'm pretty certain he has no use for them anymore~
Soldier: Damnit, you are not getting away with it!
Sherlock: Hmph, don't underestimate me~
Sherlock: Oh, so you wanna leave now? Give me my spoils before you go!
Soldier: Bastard...
Sherlock: Dare to mess with me? A bunch of idiots...
Sherlock: Let's see...what did they leave behind?
Sherlock: What the heck!? Just a bunch of cheap rations, worth pretty much close to nothing!
Sherlock: Hmph, I guess today is your lucky day. You can have all of this~
Sherlock: ...*sigh*...I guess that's it for today. I don't want those two coming back with reinforcements. Better leave now...
Sherlock: ...*sigh*...what a horrible day...
